claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table showing baseline demographic and clinical characteristics (race, sex, season, age group, influenza case status, high-risk condition) for the total cohort (N=14,590) and subgroups who received recombinant influenza vaccine (RIV4, n=3,338) versus standard-dose inactivated influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4, n=976), along with p-values for differences between RIV4 and SD-IIV4 groups. does not support the claim because the table only presents participant characteristics and contains no data on hemagglutinin (HA) content per strain in Flublok or standard-dose influenza vaccines.
